## Root Cause Analysis

- The approved HTTPS remote is reachable for read-only Git operations.
- The current environment does not expose non-interactive GitHub write credentials for HTTPS push.
- `gh` is not available as an authenticated fallback in this environment.
- The push failed before any remote update; `origin/main` remains at `5156fe6`.

## Superseded Status

- After the user pointed out the persisted SSH requirement, `origin` was restored to `git@github.com:decline-llc/netsentry.git`.
- `ssh -T git@github.com` authenticated successfully as `decline-llc`.
- This log remains as the record of the incorrect HTTPS push attempt, not as the final transport state.

## Remaining Risk

- The local `docs: reconcile release readiness blockers` commit remains local until the corrected SSH push completes.
- The documentation correction is validated locally but not yet visible on GitHub.
- Version tag `v0.1.0` must not be created until the documentation commit is pushed and the remaining evidence gates pass.

